The paper deals with optimization problems on graphs, specifically the traveling salesman problem and the 2-edge-connected spanning subgraph problem. This suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.CG (computational geometry). The use of polyhedral analysis and linear programming also suggests categories such as cs.CC (computational complexity) and cs.GT (discrete mathematics). Finally, the paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which could place it in the category of cs.OC (optimization and control).
